Get Entity history

Source: R/Entity-functions.R
get_history.Rd

Get the history data of a given Entity. If a Container object is given then this will return a list of data.tables or NULL if an Entity in the Container doesn't have any history data.

get_history(x, ...)

# S3 method for Container
get_history(x, ...)

# S3 method for Entity
get_history(x, ...)

Arguments

x

An R6 object that belongs to one of these classes: Entity, Population and World.
...

(not being used) dots

Value

a list of data.table or NULL.

Examples


create_toy_world()
#> [04:20:21] WARN  dymiumCore .subset2(public_bind_env, "initialize"): Creating a `hhsize` column in `hh_data` as it is not provided.

add_history(world$get("Individual"),
            ids = 1:100,
            event = "test_event1",
            time = 1)

get_history(world)
